<item>
            <title>[OAK-2354] Support comments anywhere in a SQL-2 statement</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-2354</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently, /* C-style comments */ are supported at the end of SQL-2 statements. They should be supported anywhere in the query.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;XPath queries can&apos;t support such comments, as &quot;/*/&quot; is valid syntax.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
